Durban - The trial of a KwaZulu Natal man charged for a rape he allegedly committed almost 42 years ago is set to get underway in the Pinetown Magistrate's Court today. 
 

 The man cannot be named until he pleads. 

 

 According to National Prosecuting Authority spokesperson Natasha Ramkisson - 
 Kara, the accused faces two counts of rape, two counts of indecent assault, crimen injuria and indecent or immoral act with a person under the age of 16.

 

 According to the charge sheet the man is alleged to have committed the rape between the period of 1977 and 1987 in the Northdene and Paradise Valley area. 

 

 In the second rape charge the complainant was under the age of 16. It is alleged that the rape took place in Empangeni between the period of 1999 and 2005. 

 

 The complainants said they were raped more than once by the accused. 

 

 He is alleged to have performed various lewd acts on his victim/s and also attempt to commit immoral acts with girls between the ages of 7 and 13. 

 

